      "text": "Spatial actors are arranged in a scene graph hierarchy, with child actors applying their transforms on top of the transforms of their parents. Only use AM_Spatial for actors that are relatively stationary – it doesn't apply any view-side interpolation to smooth out irregular movement. For moving actors, use AM_Smoothed instead.\n\n**Note**: AM_Spatial must be paired with PM_Spatial in the pawn."
